Planning

Recruitment
Aiming for 6 participants with a range of ages, gaming backgrounds and prior FlappyBird experience 

The FOCUS GROUP will begin with outlining the game, its objectives and its controls

Each player will play the game individually for 5 minutes
Partipants will voice thoughts, feelings and challenges encountered during the gameplay

We will then facilitate a group discussion on group likes, dislikes, experiences and impressions

Key questions:
1. "How intuitive were the game controls?"
2. "Did you find the difficulty level appropriate?"
3. "What aspects of the game did you enjoy the most/least?"

Facial expressions and body language during gameplay will be recorded

Users are encouraged to play around with menu, start and re-start the game and evalauate its usability. 

Data analysis will be undertaken on the feedback. 
